# rbxlAnimate — environment variables
#
# Local demo / GitHub Pages static site:
#   Email sign-in works without any secrets.
#   Real OAuth (GitHub / Google / Roblox) needs a backend — static Pages cannot
#   safely use client secrets in the browser.
#
# For local preview of the Pages build (with /RbxlAnimate basePath):
#   set GITHUB_PAGES=true
#   npm run build

# --- Optional: polish login UI “Ready” badges (still no real OAuth on Pages) ---
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GITHUB_OAUTH=true
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_OAUTH=true
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ROBLOX_OAUTH=true

# =============================================================================
# Roblox OAuth — where to put Client ID / Secret
# =============================================================================
# 1. Create an OAuth app at: https://create.roblox.com/dashboard/credentials
#    (Creator Dashboard → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 applications)
# 2. Set redirect URL to your backend callback, e.g.:
#      http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/roblox
#      https://YOUR_DOMAIN/api/auth/callback/roblox
# 3. Put the values in a local file named `.env.local` (never commit secrets):
#
ROBLOX_CLIENT_ID=
ROBLOX_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# Also used by Auth.js / NextAuth when you run a Node server (not static Pages):
# NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000
# NEXTAUTH_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-string
#
# Same pattern for other providers (server-side only):
# GITHUB_ID=
# GITHUB_SECRET=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
#
# GitHub Actions / Vercel / Railway: add the same keys as encrypted secrets /
# environment variables on the host — never ship ROBLOX_CLIENT_SECRET to the
# static GitHub Pages bundle.
